                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="6v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Calendar</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p> Important events are noted by various late medieval scribes, for example:</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1v" to="1v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Anno milleno cd scilicet l que secundo portauit varia dampna satis skania</quote> (memorial verse about <persName>Karl Knutsson</persName>'s campaign in<placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100327"> Scania</placeName>
                                        <date when="1452"/>) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Anno domini mcdlxxiii combusta est ecclesia Strengnensis cum campanis organis et quibusdam ymaginibus una cum claustro ordinis predicatorum capella sancti Eskilli magna multitudine populi et tota ciuitate duodecim curiis prelatorum et canonicorum exeptis casuali incendio circa meridiem Sabato Dominice Trinitatis</quote>
                                    </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2v" to="2v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Anno domini mdprimo obiit venerabili in christo pater dominus Conradus rogge Episcopus Strengenensis decretorum doctor Qui ecclesiam ipsam pro magna parte ex vtrique parte amplicare fecit choro et prebenda sancti erici decorauit Summum altare cum tabula regula mitra baculo pastorali et antependiis precioribus perornauit</quote>
                                    </p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3r" to="3r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Anno domini mdxxxv<hi rend="super">o</hi> In crastino iohannis ante portam Latinam Sexta feria infra octavam ascensionis domini hora 3a post prandium Combusta est tota ciuitas Strengenensis casuali incendio cum capellis Demptis dumtaxat Ecclesia cathedrali monasterio predicatorum Sola domo lapidea domini Episcopi non tamen sine grandi dampno et periculo cum nonnullis curiis ruinosis et paucis domibus in parte occidentali omittatis deo auxiliante</quote>
                                    </p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="7r" to="124r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Martyrology</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="7r" to="7v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Instructions for use of the Martyrology</title>
                                    <rubric>De arte inueniendi qualiter sit pronuncianda luna qualibet secundum numerum suppositum singulis litteris in martyrologio et ubi singulis annis littera mutatur</rubric>
                                    <incipit>Sciendum est quod quelibet littera alphabeti</incipit>
                                    <explicit>sexto kalendas marcii</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="7v" to="8v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="uniform">Preface by St Augustine</title>
                                    <rubric>Prefacio que in pluribus libris asscribitur bede super opere martyrilogii Iste prologus alicuibi dicitur excerptus de libris beati augustini</rubric>
                                    <incipit>Festivitates sanctorum apostolorum seu martyrum antiqui patres</incipit>
                                    <explicit>sunt cariate non seruitute</explicit>
                                    <bibl>
                                        <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107439">PL 123</title>
                                        <citedRange from="599C" to="602A" unit="column"/>
                                    </bibl>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="8v" to="9r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <author>
                                        <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102688">Usuard</persName>
                                    </author>
                                    <title type="desc">Preface dedicated to Charles the Bald</title>
                                    <rubric>Epistula seu prefacio vsuardi monachi ad karolum regem super opere martirologii</rubric>
                                    <incipit>Domino regum piissimo karolo augusto vsuardus </incipit>
                                    <explicit>dignetur custodire potencia amen</explicit>
                                    <bibl>
                                        <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107439">PL 123</title>
                                        <citedRange from="599A" to="600B" unit="column"/>
                                    </bibl>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="9v" to="124r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <author>
                                        <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102688">Usuard</persName>
                                    </author>
                                    <title type="desc">Martyrology</title>
                                    <rubric>
                                        <supplied reason="omitted" xml:lang="la">K</supplied>alendis ianuarii </rubric>
                                    <incipit>Circumsisio domini nostri ihesu christi</incipit>
                                    <explicit>gladio cesa est Retinarie sancti hermetis exorziste et aliorum</explicit>
                                    <note>
                                        <p> The Martyrology has been adapted for the use of Strängnäs diocese. The solemnities of certain feast days have been changed or added, see further <bibl>
                                                <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107432">Schmid (1932)</title>
                                                <citedRange from="97" to="106" unit="page"/>
                                            </bibl>. Additional feast days, such as Scandinavian saints, as well as notable anniversaries and events have been added in the margins, for example:</p>
                                        <p/>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="15r" to="15r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Eodem die beati henrici episcopi et martiris festum duplex</quote>; <quote>Eodem die anniuersarium domini ingeualdi quondam prepositi strengnesis</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="17v" to="17v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Eodem die Anniuersarium domini thome quondam episcopi Strengensis</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="24r" to="24r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Eodem die sancti Sighfridi episcopi et confessoris festum totum duplex</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="33v" to="33v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Eodem die Anniuersarium Domini Magni andree quondam Canonici Strengensis</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="34v" to="34v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Eodem die Anniuersarium domini Thome quondam Episcopi Strengenesis</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="49r" to="49r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Eodem die Anniuersarium domini Erici Kagga Prepositi Strengenensis</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="53v" to="53v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Eodem die Anniuersarium domini Nicolai Magni prebendati Strengenesis</quote>; <quote>Eodem die Beati Erici martiris quodam illustrissimi regis Swecie Totum duplex</quote> (with drawing) </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="55r" to="55r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Anno domini 1532 Incepta est Missa primalis swecana in ecclesia Stregenensi feria quinta pentecostes</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="58v" to="58v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Anniuersarium domini Ingeualli prebendati Strengensis</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p/>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="76v" to="76v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Eodem die sancte elene martyris vesgocie festum duplex</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="92v" to="92v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Dominica proxima post lamberti habeatur anniuersarium Reuerendi in christo patris domini Conradi Episcopi alme ecclesie Strengnensis.</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p> According to <bibl>
                                                <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107436">Wiktorsson (2015)</title>
                                                <citedRange from="32" to="32" unit="page"/>
                                            </bibl>, this and some other notes are written by <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102698">Nils Petersson Bang</persName>, canon in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100106">Strängnäs</placeName>
                                            <date from="1493" to="1542">1493–1542</date>.</p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="98v" to="98v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Eodem translacio sancti eskilli episcopi martiris festum duplex</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="99r" to="99r" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Eodem die beate Birgitta patrone Swecie festum duplex</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="100v" to="100v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>Item Octaue sancti Eskilli episcopi et martiris festum duplex</quote>
                                        </p>
                                        <p/>
                                    </note>
                                    <listBibl>
                                        <bibl>
                                            <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107439">PL 123</title>
                                            <citedRange from="601" to="987" unit="column"/>
                                        </bibl>
                                        <bibl>
                                            <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107440">PL 124</title>
                                            <citedRange from="9" to="857" unit="column"/>
                                        </bibl>
                                    </listBibl>
                                </msItem>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
                        <physDesc>
                            <objectDesc>
                                <supportDesc material="parchment">
                                    <support>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="1r" to="124v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <material>Parchment</material>
                                            <dimensions type="leaf">
                                                <height quantity="270" unit="mm"/>
                                                <width quantity="185" unit="mm"/>
                                            </dimensions>
                                        </p>
