                                    <extent>
                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="124" unit="folios"/>
                                    </extent>
                                    <condition> Several pages are stained and dirty. Several holes throughout the volume. Certain feasts have been erased or changed, for example on <locus from="49r" to="49r" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="88v" to="88v" scheme="folios"/>. Smudge on <locus from="31v" to="31v" scheme="folios"/>. Five stubs from a medieval breviary (or similar) have been inserted in the last quire, probably as support for the damaged binding. <locus from="124r" to="124r" scheme="folios"/> badly damaged; half of the page missing.</condition>
                                </supportDesc>
                                <layoutDesc>
                                    <layout columns="1">
                                        <locus from="1" to="12" scheme="pages"/>
                                        <dimensions type="written">
                                            <height unit="mm" max="200" min="200"/>
                                            <width unit="mm" max="130" min="130"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                        <note>Guidelines in ink.</note>
                                    </layout>
                                    <layout columns="1" writtenLines="22">
                                        <locus from="7r" to="123v" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <dimensions type="written">
                                            <height unit="mm" max="170" min="170"/>
                                            <width unit="mm" max="120" min="120"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                    </layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <p>Main text in textualis formata.</p>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">
                                    <locus from="1r" to="6v" scheme="folios"/>) may be written by another hand. </handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="8v" to="9r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Bottom of page, in brown ink by a contemporary cursive hand: a text in Old Swedish about the purchase of Scania, beginning: <quote>Skanø var køpt til Swerge.</quote> A similar text is also recorded in Linköpings stifts- och landsbibliotek, MS J 77, fols 141r-142r.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="53v" to="53v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In the left margin, in black ink by a medieval hand, partially erased: drawing of St Erik with royal crown.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="Stub_1_r" to="Stub_5_v" scheme="other"/>
                                    <note>Fragment of a theological text (breviary?), with quotes from the Bible and St Augustine.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="124r" to="124r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page, in dark brown ink by a contemporary hand: <quote>Tu in nobis es domine et nomen sanctum tuum atque gloriosum inuocatum est super nos ne derelinquas nos domine deus noster deo gracias</quote> (Jeremias 14:9). After this, in light brown ink by a contemporary hand: prayer, partially lost since half of the page is missing, beginning <quote>Et ne nos inducas in temptacionem</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="124v" to="124v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Black square notation on a four-line red staff, fragmentary.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink. Rubrics in red. Capitals touched in red. Paragraph signs in red and blue.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="6v" scheme="folios"/>: Top of the pages: plain initial <quote>KL</quote> in blue and red over ca 5 lines, with flourishing in contrasting colours. <locus from="9v" to="9v" scheme="folios"/>: Puzzle initial <quote>C</quote> in red and blue over 6 lines. <locus from="7r" to="123v" scheme="folios"/>: Plain initials over 1-3 lines in red, blue and green with flourishing, sometimes in the form of flowers, in the margins.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
                        </physDesc>
